# Grade Calculation Program

## Description

This is a C program that calculates a student's total marks, average marks, grade, and pass/fail status based on marks entered for three subjects:

* Mathematics
* Science
* English

The program also validates input to ensure that marks do not exceed 100.

## Features

* Accepts marks for three subjects.
* Validates marks to ensure they are within the allowed range.
* Calculates:

  * Total marks
  * Average marks
* Assigns a grade based on the average.
* Determines whether the student has passed or failed.

## Grade Criteria

| Average Marks | Grade |
| ------------- | ----- |
| 80 - 100      | A     |
| 70 - 79       | B     |
| 60 - 69       | C     |
| 50 - 59       | D     |
| Below 50      | F     |

## Pass Criteria

A student passes if they obtain at least 40 marks in each subject.

## Compilation

Compile the program using GCC:

```bash
gcc main.c -o grade_calculation
```

## Running the Program

```bash
./grade_calculation
```

On Windows:

```bash
grade_calculation.exe
```

## Sample Output

```text
Enter Mathematics marks(out of 100): 85
Enter science marks(out of 100): 78
Enter English marks(out of 100): 90

Your Total mark is :253

Your Average is :84.333333

Your grade is A

You have Passed
```

